===========================================
        HERLIFE EXERCISE CALENDAR
===========================================

Did you know that working out in sync with your menstrual cycle can help you build more muscle, burn more fat, and feel less exhausted? 

Your hormones fluctuate throughout the month, meaning your body is primed for different types of workouts at different times.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
PHASE 1: MENSTRUATION (Days 1-5)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Your hormones are at their lowest point, and your body is losing blood and energy. Now is the time to rest and recover.

Recommended Workouts:
- Light walking
- Restorative Yoga or Yin Yoga
- Gentle stretching
- Pilates (low intensity)
- Rest days! Don't push yourself if you are feeling fatigued or cramping.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
PHASE 2: FOLLICULAR PHASE (Days 6-13)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Estrogen starts rising, giving you a steady increase in energy and stamina. You're building up to your physical peak.

Recommended Workouts:
- Light jogging or running
- Hiking
- Dance cardio
- Resistance training (moderate weights)
- Vinyasa Yoga

----------------------------------------------------------------------
PHASE 3: OVULATION (Day 14)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Estrogen and testosterone are at their absolute peak! You have the most energy, stamina, and power right now.

Recommended Workouts:
- HIIT (High-Intensity Interval Training)
- Heavy weightlifting
- Sprinting
- Spin classes
- Bootcamp style workouts
- Any new, challenging PRs (Personal Records)

*Note: Estrogen makes ligaments more lax, so be careful to warm up properly to avoid injury!*

----------------------------------------------------------------------
PHASE 4: LUTEAL PHASE (Days 15-28)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Progesterone rises, which can make you feel more sluggish. Your body temperature is slightly elevated, so you might sweat more and fatigue faster. 

First Half (Days 15-21):
- Moderate strength training
- Steady-state cardio (swimming, cycling)

Second Half (Days 22-28):
- Walking
- Pilates or Barre
- Slow Yoga
- Bodyweight exercises

